        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @psmartp- You can't not call Wenger a good manager or even a great one. You don't fluke 3 league titles. He revolutionised football in this country. Every team until a few years into Wenger's reign were playing typical English (crap) football. Not only did he change that but he also introduced nutrition as not only a respectable but important part of the game. Players from the best English teams were still going to the pub and eating fish 'n' chips. The vast majority of the English football fraternity laughed at him but both have been adopted by every team not only in the prem but the championship too. I would say however while Wenger is a great ATTACKING manager, he is a poor DEFENSIVE one whereas Mourinho isn't as good an attacking manager but a better defensive one therefore more balanced. Well balanced managers, just like teams are often the most successful and that's the type of manager we need.
